    <details>
      <summary><b>2<sup>nd</sup> complaint COUGH</b></summary>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>S: Site</strong>
          <ul>
            <li class="grey">Where do you feel the cough originating from?
              (e.g., </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="grey">deep in the chest, </li>
              <li class="grey">back of the throat)</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>O: Onset</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>When exactly did the cough start?</li>
            <li>Was the onset sudden (acute) or did it develop over time
              (gradual/chronic)?</li>
            <li>What were you doing when it first started?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>D: Duration</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>How long has the cough been present in total (days, weeks,
              months)?</li>
            <ul>
              <li>&lt; 3 wks</li>
              <li>3-8 wks</li>
              <li>&gt; 8 wks</li>
            </ul>
            <li><br>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Aggravating Factors:</b> What makes the cough worse? (e.g.,
              lying down, exercise, cold air, dust, talking, eating, time of day
              like morning or night)</li>
            <ul>
              <li>DIURINAL VARIATIONS</li>
              <li>SEASONAL</li>
              <li>POSITIONAL</li>
            </ul>
            <li><b>Relieving Factors:</b> What makes the cough better? (e.g.,
              specific positions like sitting up, warm drinks, medications,
              steam/humidity)</li>
            <ul>
              <li>DIURINAL VARIATIONS</li>
              <li>SEASONAL</li>
              <li>POSITIONAL</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <br>
        <br>
        <li><strong>A: Associated Symptoms</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Fever, chills, night sweats</li>
            <li>Shortness of breath (dyspnea), wheezing</li>
            <li>Chest pain, palpitations</li>
            <li>Runny/stuffy nose, sore throat, hoarseness</li>
            <li>Heartburn, acid taste in mouth (reflux)</li>
            <li>Fatigue, loss of appetite, weight loss</li>
            <li>Swelling in the legs (edema)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>P: Progression</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>How has the cough changed over time? Is it getting better,
              worse, or staying the same?</li>
            <li>Has the character changed (e.g., from dry to productive)?</li>
            <li>(Especially for post-treatment: How has the cough changed since
              starting the new medication/therapy?)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>P: Pattern</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Continuous:</b> Is the cough present all the time?</li>
            <li><b>Intermittent:</b> Does it come and go?</li>
            <ul>
              <li>frequency of episodes</li>
              <li>Duration of episode</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Is there a pattern related to time of day (e.g., only at night)
              or season?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>E: Effect on Life</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>How is the cough impacting your quality of life, sleep, work,
              ability to exercise, or social activities?</li>
            <li>Does it ever cause vomiting or lightheadedness?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>R: Red Flags</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><em>Cancer</em></li>
            <li>Have you coughed up any <em>blood </em>(hemoptysis)?</li>
            <li>Are you having significant, persistent SOB?</li>
            <li>Have you had any unintentional weight loss?</li>
            <li>lumps or bumps anywhere?</li>
            <li><strong>TB</strong></li>
            <li>Is the cough associated with a high <b><u>fever</u></b>?</li>
          </ul>
          <ul>
            <li>Do you have drenching night <b><u>sweats</u></b>?</li>
            <li>Are you experiencing any chest <b><u>pain</u></b>?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>S: Scale of Zero to 10</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>On a scale from 0 (no cough) to 10 (the worst cough imaginable),
              how would you rate its severity right now?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </details>
